obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `THE REVENUE COMMISSIONERS, BOMBAY ACT, 1842`
  line `A CT N O. 17 OF 1842.`
  line ----------------------------
  line `Passed by the Hon’ble the President of the Council of India in Council, on the 16 th of December, 1842,`
  line `with the assent of the Right hon’ble the Governor General of India.`
  line `A n Act relative to the number and powers of the Revenue Commissioner under the Presidency of`
  line Bombay.
  line `I. It is hereby enacted, that so much of Regulation V, of 180, of the Bombay Code, as provides that one`
  line `Revenue Commissioner shall be appointed for the Territory subordinate to Bombay, and that the Southern`
  line `Maharatta Country shall be excluded from his jurisdi ction, is repealed.`
  line `II. And it is hereby enacted, that one or more Revenue Commissioners shall be appointed for the whole`
  line `of the Territory composing the Presidency of Bombay, each of whom shall be vested with all the powers`
  line `possessed by the single Revenue Com missioner, under Regulation V, 1830, and shall be empowered to act`
  line `within the Presidency of Bombay, or over such portion as the Governor in Council of Bombay may, from`
  line `time to time, prescribe by a Order published in the Gazette.`
  line `III. And it he hereby enacted, that each Revenue Commissioner shall have such number of Deputies`
  line `and Assistants, as the Governor in Council may deem it expedient to appoint.`
  line ------------------------------------------------
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
